description: Based on a classic “pub crawl” model, the Block Party gives registrants the opportunity to move between participating exhibitors who will be serving complimentary refreshments and beverages. To add to the fun, each Block Party exhibitor will be a part of our simple “stamp collecting competition, in which registrants visit each booth to be entered in a raffle to win great prizes, including a platinum badge for SXSW 2016.

title: Bonus Round Closing Party presented by Star Citizen
description: 100 percent crowd funded, Star Citizen aims to create a living, breathing science fiction universe with unparalleled immersion... and you’re invited to follow every step of development! More than a space combat sim, more than a first person shooter and more than an MMO: Star Citizen is the First Person Universe that will allow for unlimited gameplay.
venue: Palmer Events Center 900 Barton Springs Rd

title: Cisco’s Mimosas and a Movie: How Wearables Could Power Early Cancer Detection
description: What if one invention could change the fight against breast cancer forever? What if that invention could save one life, or thousands, or the life of someone you know? Take an extraordinary journey into the world of wearables, sensor technology, and a phenomenon called the Internet of Everything, where it’s not just about the devices or the data, but the people they impact. Join Cisco as it hosts the world premiere of the trailer of DETECTED, an upcoming, indie-doc thriller about a revolutionary wearable: a bra designed to detect breast cancer. Could this technology be the secret weapon in the cancer war? DetectedMovie.com

title: Craft-Cocktail Happy Hour Presented by KitchenAid

All SXSW badges & wristbands welcome. http://www.thebritishmusicembassy.com/

title: Happy Hour: presented by Purpose
description: Join us at the SXSW Social Good Hub for Drinks with Purpose.; Purpose is a revolutionary social business that builds movements driven by people and enabled by technology. Our work includes founding, incubating, and partnering with others to create groundbreaking organizations that use mass participation to tackle complex global challenges – from climate change and LGBT rights to poverty and the humanitarian crisis in Syria. Our Webby, Fast Company Innovation by Design (and other) award-winning work changes public narratives, amplifies media coverage, influences powerbrokers, and moves both supporters and advocates to action.; This event is part of the Social Good Hub Program, learn more at http://sxsw.com/sxgood.

title: Highball- presented by Technology & Entertainment Industry Groups & Songspace
description: Please join us for Highball, an official SXSW Interactive day party featuring live music and cocktails presented by Songspace and Bank of America Merrill Lynch Technology & Entertainment Industry Groups.; This is an afternoon hang featuring curated live music, cocktails, and complimentary beverages. INSIDE: Our friends at Electric Western will be bringing their wildy successful Nashville rock and roll dance party to Austin, spinning a hand-selected mix of the most danceable popular and obscure 50s and 60s Rock and Roll, Doo Wop, Girl Groups, and Garage Rock. See why GQ Magazine crowned Electric Western hosts of "America's Most Stylish Party." OUTSIDE: Live Music from the best up-and-coming bands of 2015. HOUNDMOUTH - NPR Music Artist to See at SXSW 2015 FUTUREBIRDS - "A stunning second record" - Pitchfork MAGIC GIANT - Billboard Magazine 'Artist on the Verge' ANDREW COMBS - NPR Music Artist to See at SXSW 2015 BOOM FOREST - "Transcendently beautiful."- Adam Duritz, Counting Crows

title: International Startup Happy Hour
description: Come join us for well deserved drinks and apps on March 14 at 6PM at Hilton Salon H before you disappear into the night.; Design Terminal Budapest is hosting a Happy Hour with Parker Thompson, Partner at 500 Startups, Peter Halacsy, Co-Founder and CTO of Prezi, Gyula Feher, Co-Founder and CTO of Ustream and Patrick Vlaskovits, NYT bestselling author of The Lean Entrepreneur.; We’ll shake off a long day with a shot of Hungarian brandy and play around with some awesome new hardware including an automated brewery, remote controlled LEGO® creations and brain sensors provided by a delegation of wicked Budapest-based startups.; The International Startup Happy Hour is the official after party of the Made in Budapest panel featuring Prezi and Ustream at March 14 5-6PM at Hilton Salon K.; See you at 6pm at Hilton Salon H. Cheers!

description: This intimate, ticketed networking event takes place at Paul Qui's flagship restaurant Qui, featuring a rich menu curated by esteemed and James Beard award winning chefs Sean Brock, Paul Qui, and revered thinker and author of Modernist Cuisine, Nathan Myhrvold.; Who Can Attend: Interactive, Gold and Platinum badges.; When: 7:00pm-10:00pm on Sunday, March 15, 2015.; Where: Qui; Cost: $250. Fees include a seven course meal with wine pairings.; Reserve your spot now by adding on the the dinner feature when you register for a 2015 badge!; To purchase your ticket: Login to cart.sxsw.com. Navigate to your purchase history using the dropdown in the upper right hand corner. Click the "Get Add Ons" link next to your purchased badge. Continue through the checkout process.

description: Come and join us at the first official event hosted by Chile and promoted by the National Council for Promotion of Music.; You will meet all the Chilean delegation conformed by Ricardo Lira, Executive Secretary for the National Council for the Promotion of Music; Consuelo Cortez, Juno; Oliver Knust, Discos Río Bueno/IMI Chile; Marcelo Godoy, Discos Tue Tue; Daniel Endrei, Kli Records; Gabriela Retamal, La Tienda Nacional; Juan Ignacio Aguirre-Perocarpi, Nuku Te Mangó; Carla Arias, Quemasucabeza; Jorge Campos, El Templo Rekords; Javiera Tapia, Journalist from POTQ.; And also you will see live music from the far south of América!; Live: • Adelaida • Marineros • Pía Zapata • Safari • La Guacha

title: SXgood Kickoff Party
description: Come together to celebrate the #SXgood programming at this year’s SXSW by joining partners & supporters for the kickoff party. Mix & mingle with attendees from a range of fields, including social innovation, impact design & cause issues. Meet representatives from various organizations including United Nations Foundation, Beaconfire, +Social Good and Wonderloop. Event entertainment will be provided by Health Alliance for Austin Musicians.
venue: Austin Convention Center Room 8BC Austin Convention Center

title: SXsports Kick-Off Reception Presented by Octagon
description: Join fellow SXsports enthusiasts and Octagon for the SXsports Kick-Off Reception! Food, drink, fun and games await.

title: SXsports Overtime Party
description: Celebrate the last few hours of SXsports at the Overtime Party. Meet sports executives and fans while enjoying complimentary beverages at one of Rainey Street’s most popular bars, Clive. Close out the second year of SXsports with a bang!

title: SXsports Selection Sunday Celebration presented by Turner Sports
description: Join Turner Sports on Selection Sunday for the unveiling of the 2015 NCAA Tournament bracket. Watch championship action all day and catch the reveal of the bracket live at 5 p.m. Join Rick Fox for on-site analysis with host Matt Winer and Damaris Lewis reporting. Guests will receive expert advice while making their picks and have an opportunity to demo March Madness Live products.

title: SXsports Topgolf Challenge
description: Kick off your SXSW experience with the SXsports Golf Challenge at Topgolf! On the Thursday evening before the festival starts, tee off with fellow attendees for a night of competition and fun at the driving range.; Who Can Attend: Film, Interactive, Gold and Platinum badges.; When: 7:00pm-10:00pm on Thursday, March 12, 2015.; Where: Topgolf in north Austin. Transportation to and from the event available for an extra fee.; Cost: $85. Includes golf clubs, two drinks, food, an exclusive gift bag and more.; Reserve your spot now by adding on the SXsports Golf Challenge feature when you register for a 2015 badge!; You can also register by emailing reg@sxsw.com

title: SXsports UFC Viewing Party
description: UFC hosts an exciting night out at SXsports with an exclusive live event viewing party. Watch Women’s Strawweight champ Carla Esparza and Men’s Lightweight Champ Anthony “Showtime” Pettis defend their titles. Welcome to the Show! Drinks are on us.
venue: Hilton Austin Downtown Liberty Tavern 500 E 4th St

title: SXSW Accelerator After Awards Party

description: Come grab a cocktail, see the latest in digital, and listen to music featuring: The Cathedrals, Buffalo Sunn, The Tontons, and DJ Sean Majors.

description: It's the last hurrah of the festival and we don't do it quietly. Musical performances by TV on the Radio, Ludacris and Z-Trip!

description: The party to start them all, the infamous SXSW Interactive Opening Party is a not-to-miss event and the ideal way to get into the SXSW groove. Join us up on the Pool Terrace at the JW!
